    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-13T05:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-13T05:26:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2245</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-13T12:00:00+01:34">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1915, 12 noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>70. Germany and Bulgaria have raised the question of what the Greek Government as
                    a neutral proposed to do with regard to the Servians, English, and French in
                    case they were driven back into <pb facs="0326" n="68" xml:id="pg_68"/> Greek
                    territory. French Minister informed the new Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_SS1">Skouloudis</persName> that if a single soldier of the
                    Allies was disarmed by Greek authority the consequences would be grave.
                    Situation acute.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
